      • hasDescription

        public static org.hamcrest.Matcher<org.hamcrest.Matcher<?>> hasDescription(String expectedDescription)
        Creates a matcher of Matcher that matches when the examined matcher has the expected description. For example: 
         
     final Matcher<Matcher<?>> matcher = hasDescription("hello world");
     assertThat(matcher, hasDescription("has description: \"hello world\""));
        Parameters:
        expectedDescription - the description that must be provided by the examined matcher
        Returns:
        Instance of HasDescription matcher
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • hasMismatchDescription

        public static org.hamcrest.Matcher<org.hamcrest.Matcher<?>> hasMismatchDescription(String expectedMismatch,
                                                                                   Object actualArgument)
        Creates a matcher of Matcher that matches when the examined matcher has the expected mismatch description. For example: 
         
     Matcher<?> matcher = ...;
     Object actualArg = ...;
     assertThat(matcher, hasMismatchDescription("mismatch: explanation", actualArg));
        Parameters:
        expectedMismatch - the description expected upon mismatch
        actualArgument - the argument causing the matcher to mismatch
        Returns:
        Instance of HasMismatchDescription matcher
        Since:
        0.1.0
